A Twitter user had come on the app to cry for help after the officers allegedly stopped him and extorted the money from him.



The spokesperson of the state police command, SP Benjamin Hundeyin, stepped into the case and after a detailed investigation, the erring officers were arrested.



Hundeyin apologised to the Twitter user and added that the officers will face disciplinary action.



















































